    '<h1>What are Cookies?</h1>
<p>Cookies are small text files stored on your computer, tablet or mobile phone. They do NOT harm the computer or the security system and, contrary to erroneous opinion, have nothing to do with viruses such as Trojans. When you visit the site, cookies allow the site to "remember" you and your preferences to improve the quality of interaction with the site.</p>
<p>More information about cookies can be found on the Internet.</p><br>
<h2>How can I control the settings that allow the use of cookies?</h2>
<p>If you do not want to receive cookies, you can change your browser settings so that it notifies you when you receive these files, or completely refuse them. You can also delete already saved cookies.</p><br>
<h2>How we use cookies</h2>
<p>We use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Inc. (Google). This service uses cookies to analyze the interaction with the site in order to improve the quality of service.</p>
<p>Our site uses the so-called user ID, which serves to identify customers in Google Analytics. Based on your behavior, Google creates a profile for your user ID. Google Analytics tracks the actions of anonymized users on different devices (tablets, PCs, smartphones, etc.).
